The Chronicle    Leonard Ncube, Online Reporter ATHLETES from the seven districts in Matabeleland North are gathered at Mosi-oa-Tunya High School in Victoria Falls for the National Association for the Secondary Heads Association (Nash) track and field events. <img class="alignnone wp-image-685851 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-5-1-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-5-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-5-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The inter-district competitions started this morning with long distance. Some of the field events will spillover to tomorrow for relay and other field activities. <img class="alignnone wp-image-685848 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/p22-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/p22.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/p22-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Officials said all districts sent teams and expectations were high that the province will be able to come up with a team to represent it at the national finals to be held in Marondera at Peterhouse College on March 22 and 23. The competitions are a culmination of zonal finals held recently. <img class="wp-image-685854 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-6-1-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-6-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-6-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Hundreds of sport lovers converged on Mosi-oa-Tunya High School for the Matabeleland North Nash track and field inter district competitions The track and field events are made up of 16 year olds and Under, Under 17s and Under 20s as well as the Paralympics category for those living with disability. “These are inter-district competitions for all districts in Matabeleland North and we have done quite a number of field events and tomorrow we will look largely at relays,” said Gamuledu Ncube, the provincial vice chair in charge of sports, and  head of Gloag High School in Bubi District.